The paper discusses access control and security in the context of dynamic coalitions, which are temporary interconnections of autonomous agents. This topic is closely related to computer security (cs.CR) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses formal modeling and verification of processes, which falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper discusses the usefulness of the Abstract State Machine (ASM) method, which is a formal method for software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL).
